.el .ds Aq '
.TH g-config-set 1  "g-config-set " 
.SH NAME
g\-config\-set \- Set a config key, validated against the editable schema
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBg\-config\-set\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIKEY\fR> <\fIVALUE\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Set a config key, validated against the editable schema.
.PP
Comments and formatting in `config.toml` are preserved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIKEY\fR>
Dotted key path, e.g. `ui.log_limit` or `ui.theme`
.TP
<\fIVALUE\fR>
New value.  Booleans accept `true`/`false`/`yes`/`no`/`on`/`off`. Enums must match one of the documented choices
